var Taylor = Artist(name: "Taylor Swift", ProfileImage: "Taylor1", DescriptionImage: "Taylor2", Description: #"Taylor Alison Swift, born December 13th, 1989, is an american Singer-Songwriter famous for her narrative storytelling and confessional lyrics. Born in West Reading, Pennsylvania, she moved to Nashville, Tennessee to persue a carreer in music. Starting in country music, Swift began her journey with her self-titled album in 2006, she reached stardom with her next album's (Fearless) singles, "You Belong With Me" and "Love Story". After the second album acclaim, she adventured in a more pop oriented sound with her third and fourth albums, "Speak Now" and "Red". In 2014, she went full pop with the album "1989", which cimented her as a part of popular culure. She followed the tremedous sucess with "reputation", which told the story of her cancelation in the summer of 2016 and how her personal life and self-image was affected by the occurence. With singles like "Look what you made me do" and "End Game", Swift changed her sound from a maximalist pop to a more urban and dark atmosphere. In full contrast, "Lover", her next album was filled with songs with a happier and more energetic beats, seen in the singles "You Need To Call Down" and "Cruel Summmer". With the the Lover tour not being able to star, Swift changed her sound once more to fit the situation the world was facing. Her music became calmer, retrospective and folk-like in Folklore and Evermore, granting her a level of acclamation never seen before. Singles like "Cardigan" and "Willow" showed a different side of her to the public. Now, Swift has a new album returning to pop, "Midnights", but with a mixture of the folk sound she mastered in her previous work; and two of rerecordings of her previous works. Breaking records at every time she releases a new album, Taylor Swift has made herself part of the history of american music."# , Musics: [Music(title: "Anti-Hero", time: "3:24", image: "Taylor3"), Music(title: "Bejeweled", time: "3:15", image: "Taylor3"), Music(title: "Lavender Haze", time: "3:31", image: "Taylor3"), Music(title: "Midnight Rain", time: "2:59", image: "Taylor3")])

var FlorenceTheMachine = Artist(name: "Florence + The Machine", ProfileImage: "Florence1", DescriptionImage: "Florence2", Description: #"Florence + The Machine are an English indie rock band that formed in London in 2007, consisting of lead vocalist Florence Welch, keyboardist Isabella Summers, guitarist Rob Ackroyd, harpist Tom Monger, and a collaboration of other musicians. The band's music has received acclaim across the media, especially from the BBC, which played a large part in their rise to prominence by promoting Florence and the Machine as part of BBC Music Introducing. At the 2009 Brit Awards they received the Brit Awards "Critics' Choice" award. The band's music is renowned for its dramatic, eccentric production and Welch's powerful vocals.The band's debut studio album, Lungs, was released on 6 July 2009, and held the number-two position for its first five weeks on the UK Albums Chart. On 17 January 2010, the album reached the top position, after being on the chart for twenty-eight consecutive weeks. As of October 2010, the album had been in the top forty in the United Kingdom for sixty-five consecutive weeks, making it one of the best-selling albums of 2009 and 2010. The group's second studio album, Ceremonials, released in October 2011, entered the charts at number one in the UK and number six in the US. The band's third studio album, How Big, How Blue, How Beautiful, was released on 2 June 2015. It topped the UK charts, and debuted at number one on the US Billboard 200, their first to do so. The album reached number one in a total of eight countries and the top ten of twenty. Also in 2015, the band was the headlining act at Glastonbury Festival, making Welch the first British female headliner of the 21st century. Florence and the Machine's sound has been described as a combination of various genres, including rock and soul. Lungs (2009) won the Brit Award for Best British Album in 2010. Florence and the Machine have been nominated for six Grammy Awards including Best New Artist and Best Pop Vocal Album. Additionally, the band performed at the 2010 MTV Video Music Awards and the 2010 Nobel Peace Prize Concert."# , Musics:[Music(title: "King", time: "4:40", image: "Florence3"), Music(title: "Free", time: "3:55", image: "Florence3"), Music(title: "Choreomania", time: "3:33", image: "Florence3"), Music(title: "Back in Towm", time: "3:56", image: "Florence3")])

var Drake = Artist(name: "Drake", ProfileImage: "Drake1", DescriptionImage: "Drake2", Description: #"Drake, whose real name is Aubrey Drake Graham, is a Canadian rapper, singer, songwriter, actor, and entrepreneur. Born on October 24, 1986, in Toronto, Ontario, Drake first gained recognition for his role on the Canadian teen drama series "Degrassi: The Next Generation." As a musician, Drake has become one of the most successful artists of the 21st century. He has released several chart-topping albums, including "Thank Me Later," "Take Care," "Nothing Was the Same," "Views," and "Scorpion." He is known for his smooth flow, introspective lyrics, and ability to seamlessly blend different genres of music, including hip hop, R&B, and pop. Drake has also collaborated with numerous other artists, including Rihanna, Future, Lil Wayne, and Travis Scott. Some of his most popular songs include "Hotline Bling," "One Dance," "God's Plan," and "In My Feelings." In addition to his music career, Drake is also a successful entrepreneur. He founded the OVO Sound record label and clothing line, and has invested in several companies, including the e-sports organization 100 Thieves. Drake has won multiple Grammy Awards, Billboard Music Awards, and other honors throughout his career, and is widely regarded as one of the most influential musicians of his generation."#, Musics: [Music(title: "God's Plan", time: "3:18", image: "Drake3"), Music(title: "Jaded", time: "4:22", image: "Drake3"), Music(title: "In My Feelings", time: "3:37", image: "Drake3"),Music(title: "Finesse", time: "3:02", image: "Drake3"), Music(title: "That's How You Feel", time: "2:37", image: "Drake3")])

var BillieEilish = Artist(name: "Billie Eilish", ProfileImage: "Billie1", DescriptionImage: "Billie2", Description: #"Billie Eilish is an American singer, songwriter, and musician who rose to fame in 2015 with her debut single "Ocean Eyes." Born on December 18, 2001, in Los Angeles, California, Billie grew up in a family of musicians and was homeschooled along with her brother Finneas O'Connell, who is also a musician and producer. Billie's music is known for its haunting, introspective lyrics and minimalist, moody soundscapes that blend elements of pop, alternative, and electronic music. She often collaborates with her brother Finneas, who produces and co-writes many of her songs. Some of Billie's most popular songs include "bad guy," "bury a friend," "when the party's over," and "everything i wanted." She has won numerous awards, including multiple Grammy Awards, and is known for her unique sense of style, which often involves oversized clothing and bold hair colors. Billie has been open about her struggles with depression, anxiety, and Tourette syndrome, and has used her platform to raise awareness about mental health issues. She is also an advocate for environmental causes and has been vocal about the need for action on climate change."#, Musics: [Music(title: "Getting Older", time: "4:04", image: "Billie3"), Music(title: "Happier Than Ever", time: "4:58", image: "Billie3"), Music(title: "Therefore I am", time: "2:53", image: "Billie3"), Music(title: "Billie Bossa Nova", time: "3:16", image: "Billie3"), Music(title: "Everybody Dies", time: "3:26", image: "Billie3")])

